Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.75,0:15:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is already present so if you value then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.87,0:15:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration you'll find yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,going through the world being polite
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.44,0:15:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,saying thank you saying thank you is fun
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were in some restaurant and they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.69,0:16:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,had pan-fried trout pan-fried trout it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.34,0:16:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,was the best pan-fried trout I've ever
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.13,0:16:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,eaten usually I don't get pan-fried trout
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.70,0:16:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got little bones and stuff anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.25,0:16:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a pan-fried trout so anyway it was
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.01,0:16:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a knockout so on the way out I went back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.91,0:16:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and said to the chef
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that's the best pan-fried
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.05,0:16:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,trout I've ever had in my life I mean he
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.41,0:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,just went boom it just beamed he was so
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,happy I can tell you went home to his
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,wife that night and says the customers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.10,0:16:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are telling me how good a cook I am you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,know I mean and then you realize how
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.03,0:16:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,rare that is how rare that is how rare
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.86,0:16:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it is where people even you know to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.71,0:16:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,express their joy back to people
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody knocks their brains out to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.71,0:16:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,shine your shoes and you don't say man
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.57,0:16:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the best job I've ever seen you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.80,0:16:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,know I mean just those simple things to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.96,0:16:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,be gracious to be to confirm for other
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.42,0:17:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,people their joy in life their value in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.83,0:17:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,life that what they're doing is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.17,0:17:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciated to see because whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.63,0:17:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they're doing is there is no scale of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.64,0:17:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,worth on the things you do action has no
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.14,0:17:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,scale of worth the simplest thing can be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.27,0:17:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,critical you know somebody holds the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.66,0:17:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,dumpster up for you and your back is up
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.14,0:17:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,out and did somebody hold the dumpster out up the hill for you, you know, because you're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.31,0:17:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying how you're going to get it up there and then suddenly you find it's up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.99,0:17:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So those little joys of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.63,0:17:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So you reflect back to the world that which you envision as the qualities that you admire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.09,0:17:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In that way you quickly go up the scale of consciousness which just disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.48,0:17:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.72,0:18:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,People think, oh it's going to take lifetimes and lifetimes and lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.08,0:18:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well the way it used to be, it probably did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.99,0:18:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowledge about consciousness was extremely limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A few gurus existed but they lived in ashrams and enclaves, had little exposure to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and often had peculiar requirements, weird food, crazy headdresses, odd strange things
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.07,0:18:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to do and eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.33,0:18:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Funny ways to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.93,0:18:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all form.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.93,0:18:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're seeking is the formless which is a realization, it's an awareness which
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.94,0:18:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,comes upon you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.88,0:19:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a cloud that envelops you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.25,0:19:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People think enlightenment is over here and I'm going to grab it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.20,0:19:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a cloud, a miasma that gradually takes you over and then suddenly, how long
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.72,0:19:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,does it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,From down here to way up there, a tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.30,0:19:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A tenth of a second, let's see, I don't have permission on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.22,0:19:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A tenth of a second is correct at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.48,0:19:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A tenth of a second is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.18,0:19:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,One instant is this way, the next instant a totally different universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.70,0:20:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes one tenth, one one-hundredth of a second, one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.14,0:20:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all the longer it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.58,0:20:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So why worry about lifetimes when it only takes one ten-thousandth of a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.34,0:20:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when the willingness is total and complete, then it happens automatically of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.50,0:20:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.96,0:20:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.96,0:20:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you pull out the last prop, you pull out the last prop, and the door swings
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.77,0:20:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,open.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.48,0:20:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't require effort, doesn't require suffering, doesn't require agony, doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.01,0:20:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,require penance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.11,0:20:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It also needs the teacher to tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.18,0:20:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.81,0:20:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can skip all those steps without feeling guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.51,0:21:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way from the bottom to the top can be very rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.72,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So people get discouraged.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, well, I've been meditating for years and then they're this, they're at this and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,they're at that place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.30,0:21:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.73,0:21:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.23,0:21:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So not to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.52,0:21:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness of its own seeks the realization of its own self-identity as the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.66,0:21:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The movement overall of human consciousness is progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going with the stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing you're going with the stream and not against the stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.70,0:21:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Human consciousness is evolving.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.48,0:21:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.48,0:21:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.48,0:21:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,said before the last time the last Harmonic Accordance in October 14th in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.85,0:21:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,San Francisco the consciousness level of mankind went from 205 to 207 all by
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.57,0:22:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. What can we do to change the world? The first thing you can do is do
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.42,0:22:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the world a favor and don't try to change it. The naive person tries to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.61,0:22:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,change the world. Now wisdom teaches you to change yourself. Change yourself. You
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.46,0:22:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to bother changing the world. And the world is serving its karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.48,0:22:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose. So why would you want to change it anyway? If you relieved all suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.58,0:22:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all war, all poverty, and all this and there wouldn't be any people here. Where
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.07,0:22:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,would you go to evolve in consciousness? I mean this is the ultimate teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.59,0:22:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,ground. And this you can go from people who are
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.74,0:22:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,lower than a Komodo dragon on their calibrated level consciousness to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.18,0:23:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ himself. So what more do you want? Here you've got a springboard. Here you've
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.09,0:23:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,got the the perfect school, you know, staging area. So I look at human
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.36,0:23:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,population on the earth as a staging area. Is there anything you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.61,0:23:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,change about it? No. You know they got Pepsi, espresso
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.79,0:23:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee, they've got coffee, they've got coffee, they've got coffee, they've got
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.44,0:23:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee. There's nothing I want to change. Why? Because each thing is serving its
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose. Each thing, each of us is born with an already calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.02,0:23:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. If your calibrated level of consciousness is 70, you're not going
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.59,0:23:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to come here if this has become a celestial realm due to all the do-gooders.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.57,0:23:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This will not be inhabitable by us who are trying to get off being miserable,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.63,0:24:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,cowardly, sneaky cheaters. Where we gonna go to learn that honesty is the best
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.85,0:24:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,policy? Where's this guy here gonna go? He needs Enron and WorldCom. Martha Stewart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.53,0:24:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He needs it. Those people need that, where else you're gonna crash. You run this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,number is about 190. They're on about 190. You run 190 to its ultimate end, and then you embrace it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.18,0:24:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you run this number is about 190. They're on about 190. You run 190 to its ultimate end, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.31,0:24:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you hit the wall. Bang! You hit the wall. That's the purpose of it. So if we didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.31,0:24:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,have an Enron or a WorldCom or whatever, we'd have to create one. So we can stop making
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the world wrong and being judgmental about it if we see that it serves the ultimate karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.74,0:25:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose. Free will choice is so unlimited because you have a whole panorama. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.51,0:25:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,go down here from killing yourself and a busload of children in the name of God. In
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.31,0:25:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of God, you're going to blow up a busload of children. That's a tough one to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.57,0:25:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,sell yourself. But by doing that, I go to heaven, then screw you kids because I got
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.35,0:25:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,30 virgins waiting for me. He's going to blow up a busload of kids so he can have 20 virgins
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.66,0:25:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or 75 virgins. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.24,0:26:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,75 for young guys, 20 virgins. The other thing they don't tell you is that those virgins
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.07,0:26:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,are 900 years old too. And they're ugly and toothless. And they hate men. I've got your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.74,0:26:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,dairy. Tell them those are the virgins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.48,0:26:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one reason they're a virgin. Okay. And you get there after blowing up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.02,0:26:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the busload of kids and they say, okay, too. Okay, boy, go to it now. Go to it. And you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.93,0:27:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,better perform or else. No Playboy magazines in heaven. No. So from the, from the most
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.01,0:27:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to the lowest, what we look at is the lowest level of the consciousness then, which are
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.90,0:27:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily primitive, the residual of the animal brain. The difficulty with an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.76,0:27:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,brain is when you put a free frontal cortex on it. Now it becomes a very clever animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.03,0:27:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you teach this clever animal with a brain of a dinosaur religion. That's what you've
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.85,0:27:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,got.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.96,0:27:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a dinosaur brain. You've taught it religion. And now it eats you in the name
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.21,0:28:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of God. That's the condition of the world. All right. So on the one hand, it's humorous.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.03,0:28:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when you put it all together and because all of it is humorous, if it was reality
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.78,0:28:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,would be sad, but it's not reality. And that's why people come here used to discover what
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.57,0:28:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.11,0:28:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is not real. Each and everything then fits together perfectly. The karmic debt
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.96,0:28:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 30 children in the bus just got paid off. Right? So each thing is perfectly in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.33,0:28:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,accord with everything else. That which gets blown up had the karma of getting blown up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.50,0:28:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or it couldn't have been blown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.32,0:29:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? Because nothing happens by accident. The infinite field of consciousness is like
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.02,0:29:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite electrostatic magnetic field of infinite power. Each one that comes in has
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.50,0:29:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a karmic inheritance, a karmic pattern. Within that infinite field, then, the karmic pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.17,0:29:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can only go where the pattern takes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.32,0:29:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And iron filing cannot be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.97,0:29:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only defy a giant electromagnetic field of infinite power. The iron filing can't say,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.18,0:29:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided I don't want to go this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.24,0:29:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've decided I don't want to go this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.66,0:29:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, each thing can only be then the fulfillment of its own karmic propensity. And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.72,0:30:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is in accord with everything else in absolute perfection. To see imperfection,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.17,0:30:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is a projection the dance of Shiva then how you see it is it terrible is it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.18,0:30:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful is it terrible is it wonderful and if I want it and if I don't want it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.07,0:30:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,terrible I like it it's wonderful that out there is hasn't moved at all it's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.70,0:30:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the same so we become then the reflection of that which we hold with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.81,0:30:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reverence therefore to review and revere those qualities means you automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.24,0:31:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in due time become them that which you hold in mind that which you worship that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.55,0:31:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which you deify that is what you become that's what you reflect by choice
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.57,0:31:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.33,0:31:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.50,0:31:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,field of infinite frequencies and vibrations that accompany all these
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.35,0:31:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,attitudes and views and emotions so what happens is that you become the automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.00,0:31:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence you become the reflection of the field no longer a person stop
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.54,0:31:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about yourself as a person or an identity because you aren't that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.36,0:31:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway your karmic wind-up toy let loose
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.18,0:31:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A karmic wind-up toy, let loose in a world of infinite possibilities and infinite gradations
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:32:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of energies, so you automatically float to the locus of maximum benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.48,0:32:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is born under circumstances that are karmically perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.46,0:32:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got a resentment about the circumstances of your birth?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.66,0:32:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you've been to the lecture before, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.06,0:32:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.06,0:32:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances of your birth are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.56,0:32:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever impairments you have, whatever the circumstances, they are the most propitious
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.08,0:32:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for your own karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.02,0:32:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why self-pity is invalid, because you don't know it, but you're born with a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.53,0:32:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,certain calibrated level of consciousness under circumstances that are most propitious
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.33,0:32:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.64,0:32:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if that's the fact for you, then it's a fact for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.35,0:32:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.57,0:33:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.85,0:33:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You left people to die of starvation and slaughtered them mercilessly, then you're going to get
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.41,0:33:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,born in a place where you left to die of starvation and slaughtered mercilessly, and now you just
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.48,0:33:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,undid that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.79,0:33:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So then you see that the world is like a theater of maximum benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.61,0:33:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that you have the option to stop identifying as an isolated being.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.52,0:33:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that you have the option to stop identifying as an isolated person, you know, a linear definition, and become just the reflection of the qualities that you respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.47,0:33:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you respect honesty, hard work, and responsibility, then you'll automatically be to work on time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.40,0:33:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll automatically finish the project, you'll automatically give the boss his due for your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.83,0:34:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,pay, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.74,0:34:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You automatically become integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.83,0:34:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.83,0:34:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If integrity is what you value, you become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.15,0:34:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you become generosity, lovingness, the desire to see the sacredness of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.80,0:34:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,life, the sacredness of all of life begins to reveal itself to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.55,0:34:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas is the joy of life coming through that birdness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.82,0:34:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The bird has learned that it's part of a relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.73,0:34:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The new game is, I tap on the branch, with a pin, and he, she taps, taps, taps with her
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.90,0:34:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,nose, bump, bump, bump.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First time she did that, I'm sitting in the chair she goes, bump, bump, bump, and I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.13,0:35:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.13,0:35:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went over, took my pen, and I went, bump, bump, bump.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.19,0:35:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She went .
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.96,0:35:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy of discovery of relationship, meaning, meaningfulness, significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.92,0:35:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You meet a new person.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.69,0:35:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you connect with those.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.84,0:35:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately she was a somebody to me, you know, and of course the joy was equal on
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.48,0:35:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this side because I realized I was a somebody to her. We just birthed a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.80,0:35:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,meaningful relationship in which you intuit the other being's joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.23,0:35:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So then life becomes the unfolding of endless discovery and joy of kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.32,0:35:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and love and responsibility and so you don't have to fight your way up the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.82,0:35:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ladder of consciousness which keeps disappearing on me. Every time I turn my
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.90,0:36:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,back on you, you notice that it disappears. It does that. I've got this wonderful, this is, no,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.92,0:36:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a real one. The calibrated levels of consciousness, as I remember way back
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.84,0:36:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 70s, it got discovered back in the 70s. And so I started to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.53,0:36:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.03,0:36:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,these are out of psychoanalysis, Columbia University Psychoanalytic School.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.51,0:36:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the emergency emotions and these are the welfare emotions classified
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.88,0:36:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by Shandor Rado back in the 30s. Also by Jung, by everyone. It's the perennial
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.48,0:36:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophy. The way these levels lay out are in accord with the perennial
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.36,0:36:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.86,0:37:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is very ancient. Mankind has always considered the stratification of these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.23,0:37:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities pretty much in that way. And you'll notice that hell is at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.92,0:37:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of the chart and divinity is at the top. It's extremely important to notice that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.94,0:37:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to God through shame, guilt, sackcloth and ashes, grief, fear of God, anger at God,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.01,0:37:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and pridefulness in how religious you are doesn't get you there. It doesn't get you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.40,0:37:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Because pridefulness in religion, et cetera, is what leads to war. So it isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.76,0:37:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that religion, which is very much in the public view, it isn't religion, it's what people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.13,0:37:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,have done with religion. What people have done with it. So we learn not to blame religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.03,0:38:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Inquisition and various other horrible things in the past as well as the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.11,0:38:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what people do with it. It's what people do with it. You can give somebody a pillow
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.15,0:38:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will enjoy it. Another person will take the pillow and smother somebody to death
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.88,0:38:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with it. So it isn't the pillow. It's what you do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.48,0:38:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That saves you making various religions wrong. Which in today's world is a temptation to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.21,0:38:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,every time you see somebody blowing off a bomb in the name of some religion, you blame
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.86,0:38:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it on the religion. No, that's the perversion. That's the misuse. That's the exploitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.34,0:38:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of things go on the camouflage of religion. It's a camouflage. All right. So
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.13,0:38:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom then we calibrated all these things and we did a scale of one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.05,0:39:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,First I started out mathematically.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.90,0:39:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The numbers got so huge mathematically that I had to switch to logarithmic. So the calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.23,0:39:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,scale of consciousness begins to ascend very rapidly and the degree of power becomes infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.67,0:39:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no longer even trackable. The energies, when they reach a certain level, become too
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.46,0:39:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful and too high a frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.36,0:39:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For the protoplasmic bilaterality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.40,0:39:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no logic nervous system, the neuronal structure to handle. And therefore there is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.15,0:39:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the birth of the pure, not the birth, but the emergence of the etheric body, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.67,0:39:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,non-protoplasmic, concordant with the physical brain, and we call it the spirit. This happens
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.71,0:40:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at consciousness level 200. So at 200 you see a whole change of quality. You see the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.32,0:40:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,courage to face the truth, the willingness to face the truth. And you see what's going
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.63,0:40:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on in consciousness is empowerment. So from here down you have force. Force, people have
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.92,0:40:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to resort to force because they don't have power. Because they don't have power and they
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.71,0:40:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,envy power. So they think they can get power by getting more money or beating up more people,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.57,0:40:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.69,0:40:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It keeps eluding them because power is of a different quality. Power is of a different
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.01,0:40:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,quality. Power. Power attracts to it exactly that which it needs. And doesn't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.76,0:41:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,anything except what the world offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.57,0:41:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is all seekingness and gain and even if it's successful, it then leads to an ego-inflation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.17,0:41:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,called pride. It leads to an ego-inflation called pride. It leads to an ego-inflation called pride. It leads to an ego-inflation called pride. It leads to an ego-inflation called pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.69,0:41:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissistic over-evaluation of oneself and arrogance. Arrogance. And the downside
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.46,0:41:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of that is, of course, quite painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.84,0:41:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We crossed over 200 and that is the critical point. We know that in America 51% of the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.51,0:41:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,people, now 51% of the people, in America calibrate over 200. 51%. The chances of meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.57,0:41:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody who's in Tigris now are 50-50 that's pretty good 50-50 in the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.78,0:42:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the world the chances are only 15% the chances in the world are 85% of the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.21,0:42:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,world caliber rates below 200 so there's no point be moaning the world when you
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.96,0:42:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,read the paper just tell yourself that's what the world below 200 looks like what
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.57,0:42:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,did you think it was gonna be a fairy dance those who live below 200 kill each
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.07,0:42:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,other routinely and if you try to stop them from killing each other they will
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.32,0:42:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,hate you they will hate you they live off of it they live out of hatred they
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.17,0:42:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,live out of the spleen and that's their livelihood that's their self
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.21,0:42:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,identification therefore you can't really deprive them of it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.07,0:42:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't really deprive them of it you can't really deprive them of it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.71,0:42:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't really deprive them of it you'll find that out try to get somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.21,0:42:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop feeling sorry for themselves you know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.34,0:43:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how difficult that is 50 years of psychiatry the toughest job in all 50
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.00,0:43:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,years was to get people off the victim-martyr roll they cling to it i
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.53,0:43:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,mean they cling to toxic and if you begin to threaten that they become very
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.09,0:43:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,hostile I am the victim by my mother treated me I am the victim of my husband
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.51,0:43:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,did to me I'm the victim of society that is the VICTIM of GENETIC AND籍KOTE
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.63,0:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Victimhood, that's the biggest addiction in our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.00,0:43:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,People think it's alcohol and drugs, forget alcohol and drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.00,0:43:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They're nothing compared to victimhood, victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.03,0:43:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,People cling to it, cling to it, cling to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.05,0:43:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Injustice, victimhood and injustice without which you can't blame anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.05,0:43:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with nobody to blame, no injustice and no victimhood and no martyrdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.05,0:43:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.32,0:44:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's the hardest one to get people off of it because the ego thrives on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.32,0:44:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego thrives on injustice and blame and self-pity and martyrdom and victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.80,0:44:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator-victim model, which is very popular in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.51,0:44:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the doorways to victimhood are jammed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.51,0:44:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The society for this and that, you know, thousands of things, all victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.15,0:44:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so then we get beyond that and we own that we're just getting, we're juicing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.32,0:44:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego loves to juice negativities.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.32,0:44:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's hard to get people off, anger, hatred, blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.32,0:44:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty years later, they're still hating and blaming a person for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.53,0:44:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the ego gets so much juice out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.53,0:44:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only juice the ego gets is the juice of negativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.53,0:44:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to take it away from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.53,0:45:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they get angry at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.57,0:45:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, America is about as popular in warring parts of the world as you would be if you go down the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.57,0:45:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear a warring couple, you know, you hear a couple down the block.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.57,0:45:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate you, Harry. I hate you, Genevieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.57,0:45:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, say you run down the block to help with these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.57,0:45:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing that happens, you're going to have a black guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.57,0:45:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're having you arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.15,0:45:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What's he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.15,0:45:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here's the one you're having, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.15,0:45:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You went down to help the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.15,0:45:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it's best to go there when they invite you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.69,0:45:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And take a third party with you, better.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.61,0:45:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so, integrity then, we enter a whole different domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.61,0:45:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel a different responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.61,0:45:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't leave the world with penicillin when nobody's, until, you know, until somebody's seen the value of the penicillin.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.65,0:45:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you feel what? A responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.65,0:45:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, something you want to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.65,0:46:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, out of love, out of love then, one does many things out of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.65,0:46:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can do things out of love that you cannot do out of anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.65,0:46:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of love for one's fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.65,0:46:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, in World War II, you know, out of love for your comrades, you'll do things that are absolutely ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.88,0:46:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You turn your back to the enemy and take a riddle full of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.15,0:46:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll take risks, you'll do things for love that you wouldn't do for anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.19,0:46:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not bravery, it's not courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.19,0:46:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because, really, love, interestingly enough, the love of men in the military for each other, or women now, calibrates at 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.23,0:46:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,510.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.30,0:46:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the sound of bagpipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.30,0:46:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of bagpipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.30,0:46:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You wonder, you feel that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.30,0:46:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The hair go up in the back of your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.30,0:46:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we calibrated it in Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.30,0:46:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.71,0:47:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,At 510, you lay down your life for your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.71,0:47:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.71,0:47:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.75,0:47:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Brotherly love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.75,0:47:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,True brotherly love.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.07,0:47:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Loving the other person as yourself, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.38,0:47:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's a very advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.40,0:47:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's one of the purposes served by the military, is you jump over 200 and will now do things out of integrity, love, and courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, everything serves something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.40,0:47:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything serves something.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.40,0:47:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can't say, isn't that terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.40,0:47:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're at war with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.40,0:47:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's this guy going to cross the line?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.40,0:47:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He left the last time out of Cardas.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.67,0:47:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, he's going to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.67,0:47:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If I got to walk into the bullets, to hell with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.88,0:47:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you walk into the bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.88,0:47:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You literally walk into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.88,0:47:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you got to literally walk into the bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.88,0:47:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you leave the body, you made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.03,0:47:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.03,0:47:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And all your buddies are there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.03,0:48:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Instant recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.03,0:48:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember doing that in the Crusades, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.03,0:48:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told you about that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.03,0:48:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, boy, I really put it through him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.03,0:48:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And he put it through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.03,0:48:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And we looked at each other and like .
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.03,0:48:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it for Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.78,0:48:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it for Allah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.78,0:48:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, we both broke into hysterical laughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.63,0:48:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.00,0:48:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.00,0:48:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.00,0:48:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it for Jesus, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.63,0:48:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.19,0:48:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And he did it for Allah, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.19,0:48:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he was very ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.23,0:48:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he was a son of a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.32,0:48:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.32,0:48:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's how we transcend the scale of consciousness, is the willingness to be the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.00,0:48:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to let go positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.00,0:48:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The need to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.00,0:48:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't just being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.00,0:49:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you need to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.00,0:49:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how that wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.00,0:49:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like needing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.03,0:49:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.03,0:49:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to be respected.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.03,0:49:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to make money.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.03,0:49:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.03,0:49:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's that neediness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.03,0:49:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the neediness that you get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.03,0:49:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you become that which attracts those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.73,0:49:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which attracts those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.73,0:49:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You build a better mousetrap and the world will come to your door.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.15,0:49:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.15,0:49:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.15,0:49:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Guarantee it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.44,0:49:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You become trustworthy, pleasant, cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.44,0:49:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they call the cleaning service, they say, I want so and so.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.88,0:49:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.88,0:49:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.88,0:49:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a couple recently that I thought were just great, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.92,0:49:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And we wanted them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.92,0:49:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you become that which would attract, that which you wish to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.07,0:49:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then automatically discover that you already are it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.07,0:49:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to seek it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.46,0:50:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You already are that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.46,0:50:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you'd tap back to broccoli, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.07,0:50:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli goes everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.07,0:50:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Broccoli goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.76,0:50:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're sitting there, you go, hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.30,0:50:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you just got it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.88,0:50:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to struggle to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.88,0:50:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Struggle to be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.88,0:50:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You already are that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.05,0:50:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you open yourself to your own infinite possibilities by owning yourself as what you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.21,0:50:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,desire to be because you are that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.21,0:50:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you haven't owned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.53,0:50:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You just haven't owned it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.78,0:50:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.61,0:50:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll go on to something less serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.80,0:50:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go on to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.38,0:50:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We changed the slides all around so I have no idea what's going to come up this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.09,0:51:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery that you could calibrate the truth of anything in time or space, that the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.09,0:51:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field of consciousness is a vibrational field of infinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.28,0:51:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes up a whole scale much like the electromagnetic spectrum to extremely high and very powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.40,0:51:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,frequencies, too high and too powerful for the human nervous system to tolerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.98,0:51:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The human nervous system can comfortably tolerate up to about 600 or 700 and from here on it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.98,0:51:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes extremely difficult and hardly anybody goes there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.98,0:51:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a few people on the planet in the 700s, nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.11,0:51:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.11,0:51:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think this is the right dimension to do it because the protoplasmic nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.23,0:51:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is not equipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.23,0:51:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not equipped to handle those high frequencies and energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.23,0:51:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people that go over this level here will complain about all kinds of aches and pains
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.23,0:52:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and react with all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.23,0:52:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated everything that could be calibrated and we found that the highest level that's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.23,0:52:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ever walked this planet was 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.46,0:52:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Highest beings were 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.26,0:52:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The scale of consciousness goes up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.26,0:52:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600, you shift over from the linear to the non-linear reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.59,0:52:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600, it's called traditionally enlightenment in which the identification with a personal
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.57,0:52:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,self as who you are dissolves and is replaced by a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.76,0:52:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's replaced by, at 600, it's replaced by bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.76,0:52:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an overwhelming bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.67,0:52:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The state is self-sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.67,0:52:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In that state, one needs nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.46,0:53:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The physiology seems to come to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.82,0:53:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't need to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.82,0:53:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't need to drink water.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.82,0:53:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't need to have to go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.82,0:53:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.59,0:53:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's even the choice to breathe or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.44,0:53:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The breathing will actually stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.44,0:53:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either breathe or not breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.98,0:53:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either hang out with the body or let it fall over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.44,0:53:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.28,0:53:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then because, I would say, of karmic propensities, some phenomenon may occur in the world in response
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.21,0:53:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to which you breathe again, that your father will think that you have just died and spend
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.80,0:53:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of his life in guilt, berating himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.80,0:53:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of caringness, out of love, then, one may breathe and re-own the bodiness again.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.88,0:53:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,600.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.88,0:53:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people leave the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.88,0:54:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They hit 650%, I think we said, will leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.88,0:54:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They just won't breathe it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.88,0:54:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then some, for strange reasons, most people will go from below down and suddenly land
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.88,0:54:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at like 700 or something, like Nisargadatta, Maharaja.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.88,0:54:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing, curious about it, is they stay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.88,0:54:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically never happens that anybody arrives at like 700 and then moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.30,0:54:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Moves on from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.71,0:54:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They stay the rest of their life at 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.71,0:54:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They did around by the mountain there or Nisargadatta, Maharaja.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.71,0:54:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They stay at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.71,0:54:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is probably smarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.11,0:54:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You come back, you move from here to there in another realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.11,0:54:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, once in a millennium, somebody will continue on up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.11,0:54:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we calibrated these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.11,0:54:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got the divinity is sort of like a step-down transformer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.11,0:54:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite power of God is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.11,0:55:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite power of God is so enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.71,0:55:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So enormous that man doesn't encounter the power of divinity directly, you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.15,0:55:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,through the nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.15,0:55:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're sort of like step-down transformers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.15,0:55:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we said, what are archangels?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.15,0:55:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.15,0:55:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.15,0:55:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to buy an archangel, it's going to cost you 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.48,0:55:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.48,0:55:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's as far as the scale goes to 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.48,0:55:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the way it graphs out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.48,0:55:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the way it graphs out in microwatts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.61,0:55:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.61,0:55:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the power in microwatts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.61,0:55:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see it goes up to infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.61,0:55:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.61,0:55:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.73,0:55:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we like to correlate the known world, the world of logic,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.73,0:55:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm, and then move from the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.73,0:55:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.73,0:56:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at 500, you're moving in from supposed objectivity
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.73,0:56:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,into subjectivity as the absolute reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.73,0:56:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,From 500 up, it's the subjective that's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.88,0:56:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,From 500 down, it's the so-called objective world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.88,0:56:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.88,0:56:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.96,0:56:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the way the world is distributed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.96,0:56:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.96,0:56:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We redrew this graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.96,0:56:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really 85% of the world calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the great mass of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.96,0:56:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the great mass of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.96,0:56:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, as the numbers gets higher,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.96,0:56:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there's fewer and fewer people on the planet, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.13,0:56:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in America, it's about 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.13,0:56:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the population on the planet then is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.05,0:56:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the great masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.01,0:56:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reading yesterday, 67% of the people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.01,0:56:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,live on $2 a day, $2 a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.17,0:56:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.21,0:57:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,67% of the people on the planet live on $2 or less,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.59,0:57:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,two American dollars or less per day, 67%.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.59,0:57:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.19,0:57:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when you get to the level, here's America, 421.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.09,0:57:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's America, 421.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.09,0:57:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see of all the people on the planet, you're just a few folks here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.09,0:57:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just a few folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.09,0:57:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go from 421 up, you see who you got to talk to.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.38,0:57:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think democracy is wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.80,0:57:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of here, bastards.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.80,0:57:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.11,0:57:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A boy in Afghanistan, I want you to vote for democracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.11,0:57:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your gun, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.32,0:57:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He just prescribed his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.32,0:57:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a gun, he's going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.51,0:58:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.51,0:58:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's where we stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.51,0:58:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives us sort of a feeling of where we are and who we are
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.51,0:58:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way we see the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.51,0:58:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.71,0:58:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,These are familiar to people who have been to these lectures before,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.71,0:58:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so just quickly we're going to review them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.71,0:58:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the 15% on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.71,0:58:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the 85% of the people, and we'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.42,0:58:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the 15% counterbalances the 85%.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.42,0:58:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is from 200 up, power increases logarithmically.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.92,0:58:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,One person at 500 is more powerful than, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.03,0:58:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 people below 200 or something like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.03,0:58:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,probably more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.03,0:58:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, the world would self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.03,0:58:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity would kill itself off.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.03,0:58:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't Russia set off the ultimate bomb
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.03,0:58:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that was going to destroy all of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.03,0:59:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They had it planned, the mega bomb, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.21,0:59:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of this 15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.21,0:59:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this 15%, propitious things happen
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.21,0:59:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that preclude man from killing himself off completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.21,0:59:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorbachev.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.21,0:59:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorbachev, without a single shot, takes down monolithic communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.21,0:59:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Cold War and all our, baring our teeth and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.21,0:59:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,was probably necessary at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.21,0:59:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but that isn't what, we didn't defeat Russia in the Cold War.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.21,0:59:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Gorbachev just pulled the prop out and it collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.21,0:59:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He's at 500, or over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.21,0:59:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One person at 500, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.40,0:59:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,can collapse the entire Russian communist regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.55,0:59:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That power of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.94,0:59:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorbachev and, who was our president then?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.03,0:59:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Reagan.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.03,0:59:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Reagan, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.03,0:59:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They were both over 500, curiously.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.11,0:59:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of them just pulled the thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.11,0:59:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole thing went .
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.19,0:59:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.19,0:59:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No war.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.19,1:00:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.19,1:00:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.19,1:00:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.19,1:00:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.19,1:00:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's the function of these people here,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.19,1:00:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to just be who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.19,1:00:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the president at that time and Gorbachev
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.26,1:00:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,were just being who they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.26,1:00:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being who they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.26,1:00:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being who they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.26,1:00:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And who they were, as a consequence,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.26,1:00:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalanced that which was going to set off the mega bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.26,1:00:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan was it would destroy all of life on this planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.26,1:00:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,permanently.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.26,1:00:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of a negative thought, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.36,1:00:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.36,1:00:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the rise of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.36,1:00:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who haven't been to these lectures before,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.36,1:00:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how the way to relate to ego is like a pet.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.38,1:00:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ego then, instead of being vilified,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.38,1:00:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of setting yourself against the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.38,1:00:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it as the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.38,1:00:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of the evolution of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.84,1:00:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a whirling ball of molten,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.84,1:01:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of thousands of degrees Fahrenheit,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.84,1:01:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,flying through the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.84,1:01:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It gradually cooled down.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.84,1:01:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A crust formed enough that matter formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.40,1:01:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the energy of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.82,1:01:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.82,1:01:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The light of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.82,1:01:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when it interacts with matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.82,1:01:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,has the propensity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.82,1:01:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality to create life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.59,1:01:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.07,1:01:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.07,1:01:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In scripture, it's the light of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.57,1:01:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of God, consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.57,1:01:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,interacts with inert matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.03,1:01:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's because of the life,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.03,1:01:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.03,1:01:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.03,1:01:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.03,1:01:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that a life arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.03,1:01:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So it does not arise as a happy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.03,1:02:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,accident of chemical reactions.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.69,1:02:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens as a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.73,1:02:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite power out of which existence arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.73,1:02:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So on this planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.86,1:02:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances of survival of life were probably slim, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.86,1:02:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's red hot in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.86,1:02:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still molten in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.86,1:02:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.86,1:02:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple thousand degrees in the middle of the earth?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.86,1:02:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right below my feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.86,1:02:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple thousand degrees down there, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.86,1:02:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So on this,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.86,1:02:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.86,1:02:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,hostile matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.86,1:02:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,life begins to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.23,1:02:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.23,1:02:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to evolve,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.23,1:02:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to be interested in survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.23,1:02:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Its primary programming has to be survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.44,1:02:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If we land on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.44,1:02:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to be our program, survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.44,1:02:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So life then,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.61,1:02:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in its earliest form,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.61,1:02:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the first conscious life is bacteria,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.61,1:02:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,does not have within it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.61,1:02:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a source of its own energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.61,1:02:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always say,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.61,1:02:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the saddest part of being a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.61,1:03:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is we're not green.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.61,1:03:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were green,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.90,1:03:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,had chlorophyll,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.90,1:03:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn't have to work or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.90,1:03:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You just walk around in the sunshine,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.28,1:03:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,recharge your batteries,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.28,1:03:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.28,1:03:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you've got to get,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.11,1:03:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to eat,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.11,1:03:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.11,1:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've got to eat,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.11,1:03:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then you've got to have something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.11,1:03:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.44,1:03:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you don't have fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.44,1:03:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we really came in here poorly prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.76,1:03:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No fur, no feathers,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.76,1:03:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't fly,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.76,1:03:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to walk,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.76,1:03:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to buy a car.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.15,1:03:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.44,1:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So to survive,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.44,1:03:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,life had to become self-interested.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.67,1:03:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.67,1:03:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.67,1:03:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in its most primitive form,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.67,1:03:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,me, me, me survival. Therefore, there's no point in making it wrong in other people or
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.51,1:04:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in yourself. It's supposed to be that way for the bacteria. So the amoeba doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.19,1:04:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy factory. The amoeba has to go out there and get energy in chemical form, whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.94,1:04:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,form. Therefore, life in its primitive form then has to acquire energy. So the first signs
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.73,1:04:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of life here are bacteria at one, and these are the archaeologic ages, which are so prehistoric
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.65,1:04:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that I can't even figure them out. The age of the oldest dated rocks is about a trillion
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.26,1:04:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,years old. I can't, too big a number to read. All right, so slowly over great eons of time
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.96,1:04:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,then, primitive life becomes more clever at acquiring energy. It learns to swim in the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.05,1:04:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ocean. It learns to swim in the ocean. It learns to swim in the ocean. It learns to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.19,1:04:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,swim in the ocean. It learns to swim in the ocean. It learns to swim in the ocean. It
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.21,1:04:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for it, learns to eat other things that have arisen at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.17,1:05:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So life, you see, is not evil, it's just
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.36,1:05:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,deficient. It has to get in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.75,1:05:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to get. Here you see we finally get up to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.44,1:05:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the dinosaurs, primitive mammals. Consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.48,1:05:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,level at this time is only, here it is in the 40s.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.98,1:05:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The rise of reptiles in the 40s.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.61,1:05:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's about Bin Laden in the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.23,1:05:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,40s, 40s to 60s, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.82,1:05:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're dealing with? The prefrontal cortex then
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.19,1:05:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,has taught this thing how to be a better reptile.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.46,1:05:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go up here, you finally get up to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.19,1:05:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,112,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.55,1:05:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of modern mammals, and then you finally get
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.42,1:05:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 212 here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.30,1:05:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And more evolved. So you see life becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.80,1:06:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more clever at survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.32,1:06:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you get to a certain level, consciousness level,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.13,1:06:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it changes form. So let's go to the next chart. It changes
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.15,1:06:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,its nature. And so here you have the bacteria we were talking
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.40,1:06:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about, and then protozoa, the arachnids,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.51,1:06:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fish, vipers. We put octopus
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.32,1:06:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in here. Where's octopus?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.30,1:06:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Octopus is 20. Anyway, so life becomes more and more
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.71,1:06:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,complex. But you still see you've got to go out there to get
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.73,1:06:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,energy to live. The polar bear has to eat. All these animals
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.13,1:06:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,have to eat. They have to get it from someplace. And we call
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.15,1:06:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,them voracious and dangerous animals. And then when you get
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.53,1:06:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to consciousness level 200, the same as in human consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.23,1:06:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,200,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.59,1:07:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a major transformation from voracious to benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.00,1:07:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly at 200, we just calibrated a whole bunch of animals.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.94,1:07:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We just did all these animals we could think of. They were not arranged
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.53,1:07:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a chart like this. We just did them random.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.19,1:07:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And Susan and I just spent one weekend doing all the animals around
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.65,1:07:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the birds around and everything else. This is animal weekend.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.01,1:07:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we arranged them according to their calibrated number.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.73,1:07:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's how they came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.25,1:07:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how they arranged themselves. You see that which is below here is carnivorous
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.25,1:07:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and voracious. It has to get. And then suddenly when you get to 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.76,1:07:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you see a shift of the kind of animals. So here are the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.01,1:07:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So here are the carnivores. And here are the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.09,1:07:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So these don't have to kill anything in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.80,1:07:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a different mechanism. And they become vegetarians.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.44,1:08:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.48,1:08:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the vegetarians can now feel superior to the non-vegetarians.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.51,1:08:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You've become as smart as the sheep now.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.72,1:08:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is serious, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.51,1:08:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The only things that are serious are things that you make serious,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.09,1:08:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, in and of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.47,1:08:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the kitty and the family cat. And of course, we did
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.39,1:08:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing that we did.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.69,1:08:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So she came in as a little girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.42,1:08:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mother was a very different from what we usually do.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.03,1:08:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We said yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.03,1:08:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She comes in as a black cat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.03,1:08:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not from the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.03,1:08:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She was born in a river or river.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.03,1:08:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a very different cat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.03,1:08:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She's one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.03,1:08:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's really a very active creature.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.03,1:08:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you see is that she's going to have a lot of meat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.03,1:08:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we put the meat in her plate.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.22,1:08:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what she's going to eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.22,1:08:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And we saw that she was going to eat the meat and the food.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.22,1:08:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to make her feel more healthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.22,1:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we had her eat the meat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.22,1:08:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a big gave her really big meal.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.22,1:08:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the meat in this one was a big meal.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.22,1:09:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So she's going to be from tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.22,1:09:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So she came in at 250. When we got her, she was, what did I say she was at? 350? Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.47,1:09:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so here you see then, these animals are more evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.81,1:09:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the effect of human interaction with the cat, it jumps five points in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.43,1:09:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The human interaction with dogs, they jump five points.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.31,1:09:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You come up to the gorilla, chimpanzees. Chimpanzees are extremely intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.69,1:09:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And here are the exceptions that we, of course, have fun with.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.18,1:09:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex, the trained African gray parrot. Dr. Pepperdine from the University down in Tucson,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.35,1:09:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who can count and knows all kinds of things, calibrates at 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.76,1:09:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And Coco, who recently had her tooth extracted.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.39,1:09:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco got that there was something wrong and the tooth wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.57,1:09:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Went to the dentist and had her tooth extracted. That was in the news a week ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.31,1:10:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And Coco had her tooth extracted.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.02,1:10:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you come to these exceptional things.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.09,1:10:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're a trained African gray. So we're tracking the African gray that we got as of present.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.43,1:10:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And she came in to us at 350.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.18,1:10:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So she had already moved up during the year and a half of her previous life.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.15,1:10:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And now in the last six weeks has moved from 350 to 355.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.88,1:10:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.01,1:10:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we're going to train her.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.65,1:10:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to train her because Alex is at 401 and we're not going to be happy, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.80,1:10:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble is Dr. Pepperdine spent months and years blue cube,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.80,1:10:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to do that with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.30,1:10:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, songbird's song at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.30,1:10:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have a puzzle that we still haven't solved.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.80,1:10:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it that a cat's purr calibrates at 500?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.30,1:10:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it that a dog's wagging tail calibrates at 500?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.43,1:11:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.43,1:11:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were in Toronto, in the front page of the paper,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.43,1:11:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I told you about it in the last lecture, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.43,1:11:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A dog by the name of Elvis.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.43,1:11:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a pretty mentally disturbed person who had a whole bunch of high-powered rifles and ammunition, 6,000 rounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.43,1:11:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was going to kill everybody in sight and then kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.68,1:11:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And Elvis was in the park and Elvis had a Frisbee in his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.68,1:11:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran over to this guy and wanted him to play.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.68,1:11:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And this guy suddenly came to his senses.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.68,1:11:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.68,1:11:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People couldn't talk him out of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.68,1:11:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Elvis, just by being what Elvis is, this guy instantly changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.68,1:11:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be going crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.68,1:11:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He threw all the guns away and he surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.68,1:11:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the power then...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.72,1:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that's 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.72,1:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's a guy who probably calibrated, what, 120 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.00,1:11:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,About to kill people.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.03,1:12:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And a 500 energy comes up and says,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.03,1:12:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Play with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.28,1:12:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, karmically, this guy had the choice at that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.28,1:12:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have shot the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.28,1:12:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people do because a couple weeks ago in Prescott or someplace like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.28,1:12:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the option was taking the other direction to shoot the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.28,1:12:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he didn't shoot the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.35,1:12:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.47,1:12:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And laid down his guns and is probably getting professional help.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.47,1:12:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.47,1:12:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see how all the...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.47,1:12:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How the world comes together like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.47,1:12:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When it doesn't meet the...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.47,1:12:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's not logical, we call it a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.84,1:12:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly was a miracle for the people that he was about to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.84,1:12:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But the miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.84,1:12:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the propensity of everything involved then moved impersonally.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.96,1:13:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And Elvis just saw the man.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.22,1:13:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And reached out to the man.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.60,1:13:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the man looked at the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.34,1:13:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how it all...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.34,1:13:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When you put it all in slow motion,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.34,1:13:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see what life is about.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.81,1:13:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to understand the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.38,1:13:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask a question about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.38,1:13:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflect on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.53,1:13:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Just hold it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.63,1:13:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then look at it in slow motion.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.17,1:13:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And its true nature just reveals itself to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.17,1:13:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As come and play with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.17,1:13:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The intrinsic innocence of all of life then reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.27,1:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you stop vilifying life because you see the innate innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.72,1:13:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The children who were brainwashed into thinking that if you blow up a busload of kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.96,1:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll go to heaven because you're serving God.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.96,1:14:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, their innate innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.96,1:14:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Hitler Youth in the 30s.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.25,1:14:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just brainwashed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.25,1:14:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, the defect is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.43,1:14:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The defect is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.43,1:14:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What the Buddha said.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.43,1:14:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What Christ said.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.43,1:14:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason to forgive people is because intrinsically everyone is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.92,1:14:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They're innocent because what you inherit as a human being then is an ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.05,1:14:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You inherit a mind which is like the hardware of a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.05,1:14:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And life then comes in and programs it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.63,1:14:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're born with hardware.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.63,1:14:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're born with the software of your pre-existing karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.78,1:14:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you now have software that has options.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.78,1:14:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the disk isn't finished yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.78,1:14:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The disk is only half done.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.78,1:14:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You come in with a certain programming.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.03,1:15:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But that man had his choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.03,1:15:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have kicked Elvis right in the chops.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.03,1:15:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Said, get away from me, you bad dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.03,1:15:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And shot him.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.03,1:15:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.03,1:15:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the option is right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.03,1:15:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you do a still life snapshot of things, it reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.03,1:15:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the beauty of photography.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.03,1:15:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The genius of photography to me is that it takes something like that and it does a stop frame.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.03,1:15:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you get to see it for what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.03,1:15:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to see it in the middle of the stop frame.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.03,1:15:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.39,1:15:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough for you folks now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.10,1:15:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to take a break pretty soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.10,1:15:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.10,1:15:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we'll take a break at 10.30.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.10,1:15:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.10,1:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,10.30?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.60,1:15:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.11,1:15:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.31,1:15:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.31,1:15:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So we got.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.31,1:15:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.31,1:15:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just wanted you to see the evolution of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.31,1:15:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend the ego, to become enlightened then, means to transcend the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.31,1:15:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you transcend the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.38,1:16:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The easiest way is by completely and totally understanding it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.38,1:16:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,By understanding its origin, how it developed and what its qualities are.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.47,1:16:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point of berating it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.47,1:16:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Listing all the negative qualities of the ego as sins.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.47,1:16:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then feeling guilty about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.47,1:16:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And berating yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.47,1:16:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And hating other people because their consciousness level is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.52,1:16:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how it evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.52,1:16:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with becoming a human being is that you inherit an animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.52,1:16:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You inherit an animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.52,1:16:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you got a prefrontal cortex plastered on the front of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.52,1:16:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't remove the old animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.01,1:16:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They now put a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.01,1:16:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of teeth and fangs, now you can do atomic bombs or bullets or machine guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.52,1:16:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf just bares his teeth and slashes the other one's throat.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.52,1:16:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We use machine guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.59,1:17:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the basic primitive animalness hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.19,1:17:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the prefrontal cortex now has just been added to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.19,1:17:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the problem of being a man?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.19,1:17:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that you got a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.19,1:17:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got the birth of spiritual awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.19,1:17:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got it birthed in an animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.19,1:17:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So self-hatred and conflict is inevitable if you're born human.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.26,1:17:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Born human.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.89,1:17:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the karma of being a human is the karmic battle between the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.00,1:17:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Between calibrated levels below 200 and above 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.00,1:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are the stage of evolution that transcends the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.00,1:17:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It owns it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.00,1:17:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual reality of its own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.00,1:17:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And we then progressively transcend the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.09,1:17:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And become and realize that we are only the spirit of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.09,1:17:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We are the energy, the spirit of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.09,1:17:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What does all this mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.65,1:18:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well of course it's all the great philosophy and discussion and epistemology and theology and metaphysics.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.65,1:18:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of religions.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.97,1:18:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Theological propositions.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.97,1:18:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Philosophic systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.97,1:18:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did the man evolve then?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.97,1:18:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So he gets a prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.97,1:18:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And now he has to make some kind of peace with his animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.97,1:18:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion certainly serves that purpose to a certain degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.97,1:18:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The one reason enlightenment is extremely rare is because religion will only take you a certain part of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.07,1:18:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then religion itself becomes the block.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.52,1:18:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion itself takes you from here to there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.52,1:18:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it becomes the block.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.52,1:18:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond which you have to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.52,1:18:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore enlightened people have traditionally been called mystics.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.52,1:18:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic then transcends the religion itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.52,1:18:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And reveals the spiritual core out of which the religion arose in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.52,1:18:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.68,1:19:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the investigation of this is interesting throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.72,1:19:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the western world of course were put together in 1955 I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.75,1:19:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,By Mortimer Adler at the University of Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.75,1:19:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With a whole group of the world's best scholars.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.81,1:19:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They still have a scholarship committee.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.81,1:19:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is still active.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.81,1:19:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And they still recommend that you study the great books of the western world over a ten year period.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.93,1:19:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They have a ten year study.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.93,1:19:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you spread it out over ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.93,1:19:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can say that you are liberally educated.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.93,1:19:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To be liberally educated takes ten years.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.93,1:19:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to have read every one of these.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.93,1:19:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And known what they meant.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.89,1:19:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.27,1:19:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I read them as a kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.40,1:19:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a misspent youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.40,1:19:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To be speckled.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.40,1:19:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Skinny.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.40,1:19:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.40,1:19:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Bifocals.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.53,1:19:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting in a big chair.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.53,1:19:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Skinny.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.53,1:19:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Reading books.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.53,1:20:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,While everybody else was playing football.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.81,1:20:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Muddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.81,1:20:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Disgusting game.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.81,1:20:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Violent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.01,1:20:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.01,1:20:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd rather read the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.01,1:20:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the misspent youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.01,1:20:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Misspent youth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.32,1:20:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.42,1:20:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you find this is very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.42,1:20:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest thinking of all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.42,1:20:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.42,1:20:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean today?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.42,1:20:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It means it set up the categories of logic, truth, and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.42,1:20:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All this was done.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.52,1:20:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Categories of logic, truth, and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.52,1:20:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Were really pretty much finished by about 350 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.52,1:20:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.52,1:20:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.52,1:20:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In later terms.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.52,1:20:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Times.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.52,1:20:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They became embellished and interpreted in greater depth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.52,1:20:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are very interesting reading.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.52,1:20:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single one of these is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.52,1:20:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And we wondered how they calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.52,1:20:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So we calibrated the great books of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.52,1:20:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I happen to have a set.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.77,1:20:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Which due to good karma I came upon in a used condition and got them cheap.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.77,1:21:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to pay for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.77,1:21:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think $500 I got.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.02,1:21:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.02,1:21:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.02,1:21:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.69,1:21:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the best thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.69,1:21:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.69,1:21:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The best thinking is also inculcated into our political system.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.69,1:21:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The constitution, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.69,1:21:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Came out of ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.69,1:21:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As we find through the philosophers.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.69,1:21:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,1600, 1700, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.69,1:21:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have the best thinking of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.69,1:21:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,From the ancient world of ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.69,1:21:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,On through the intellectual development of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.69,1:21:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the most craftily thought out government.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.69,1:21:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Political system.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.69,1:21:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Constitution.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.69,1:21:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill of rights, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.69,1:21:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Comes out of.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.69,1:21:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is distilled out of all this thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.69,1:21:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting out from Aristotle, Plato, and Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.82,1:21:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates is not on the list.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.82,1:21:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates didn't write anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.82,1:21:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He was too smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.07,1:22:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he was short and ugly and had a vicious wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.07,1:22:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.07,1:22:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't get any peace at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.07,1:22:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't write anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.07,1:22:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably because she never shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.15,1:22:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Her name was Zantippe.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.15,1:22:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And she's famous in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.15,1:22:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Socrates is.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.15,1:22:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But for other reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.15,1:22:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.15,1:22:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So Socrates calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.15,1:22:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.22,1:22:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,About 540 or 550.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.22,1:22:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's not on the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.22,1:22:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he didn't write anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.22,1:22:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.22,1:22:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.22,1:22:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What he had to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.22,1:22:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is included in Plato.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.22,1:22:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.22,1:22:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.22,1:22:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you've got all the great thinkers of all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.22,1:22:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see Aristotle at 498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.22,1:22:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.22,1:22:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And Aristotle.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.22,1:22:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.28,1:22:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.28,1:22:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.28,1:22:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.28,1:22:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.28,1:22:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.28,1:22:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.28,1:22:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.28,1:22:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.28,1:22:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.28,1:22:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.28,1:22:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.28,1:22:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.28,1:22:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.28,1:22:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,498.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.28,1:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.28,1:22:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.28,1:22:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Was at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.28,1:22:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.28,1:22:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Also.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.28,1:22:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Strangely.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.28,1:22:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Had.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.28,1:22:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.39,1:22:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.39,1:22:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In God.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.39,1:22:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.39,1:22:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Profound.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.39,1:22:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.39,1:22:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.39,1:23:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.39,1:23:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.39,1:23:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hadn't been born.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.39,1:23:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.39,1:23:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.68,1:23:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.68,1:23:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.68,1:23:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And neither.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.71,1:23:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.71,1:23:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinduism.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.71,1:23:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Had.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.71,1:23:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Through his study of truth plus his own inner intuition,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.31,1:23:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,he was committed to truth to God as divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.67,1:23:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to truth as representative of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.55,1:23:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Socrates was accused of corrupting the youth of Athens
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.35,1:23:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by teaching him such things as I'm telling you about today,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.35,1:23:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,corrupting the youth,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.97,1:23:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he was condemned to death,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.17,1:23:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was ordered to drink hemlock.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.23,1:23:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he could have bartered his way out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.76,1:23:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have hymned and hawed, backed off,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.53,1:23:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and Socrates refused.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.06,1:23:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He says he believes in God as truth, he teaches truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.15,1:23:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and he cannot negate truth in order to save his physical life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.80,1:23:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So there was a great hero long before,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.52,1:24:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and one not well recognized the greatness of Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.46,1:24:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He also said other things that have a great bearing on today's society.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.46,1:24:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so here you see the evolution then of this prefrontal cortex,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.21,1:24:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is put on the old animal brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.01,1:24:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see Francis Bacon, you see Berkeley,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.14,1:24:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great names of history,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.32,1:24:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chaucer, Copernicus, Dottie, Charles Darwin at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.93,1:24:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin is, of course, very interesting
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.64,1:24:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because Darwin, science calibrates in the mid-400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.51,1:24:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the theory of evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.68,1:24:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all of science,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.86,1:24:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mid-400s are the birthing then in the Western world of science.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.81,1:24:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The great wealth of which everybody supposedly hates America,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.77,1:24:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the great wealth and power of America
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.78,1:25:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is birthed out of consciousness level 450, 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.44,1:25:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The great wonders of science, engineering,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.94,1:25:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great discoveries.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.21,1:25:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all what America has discovered.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.81,1:25:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything from the airplane
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.02,1:25:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to just about everything else that sells anywhere in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.48,1:25:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it originated in America.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.22,1:25:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So the capital of America,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.31,1:25:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which people like to vilify,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.75,1:25:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is not money at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.56,1:25:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The capital is inventing electricity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.27,1:25:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Edison, zip,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.43,1:25:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just created more capital
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.02,1:25:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,than half the countries in the world annual income.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.89,1:25:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.85,1:25:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Think just one.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.47,1:25:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,One thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.21,1:25:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So capital is creative genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.22,1:25:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Ford, you can name one after another.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.43,1:25:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Westinghouse.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.06,1:25:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who invented the cotton gin.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.14,1:25:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Invention, creativity, and genius, that's capital.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.64,1:26:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to take something with you that's worthwhile,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.22,1:26:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you take one brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.14,1:26:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And from that, you can put me anywhere on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.72,1:26:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll start all over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.88,1:26:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Put me on a deserted island in the middle of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.47,1:26:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back in two years, you'll see employment.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.34,1:26:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm manufacturing swings and coconut fruities.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.63,1:26:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So creativity, inventiveness, then genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.15,1:26:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is capital?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.65,1:26:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Capital is genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.53,1:26:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The money is automatic because, as I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.61,1:26:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you will just be what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.77,1:26:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the consequences are automatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.88,1:26:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you invent a gasoline engine, if you invent an airplane,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.64,1:26:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll create a whole new industry.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.72,1:26:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the world really envies, although they don't know it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.77,1:26:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't want to face it,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.53,1:26:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is the genius of creativity and the value
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.97,1:27:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that we give to individuality and creativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.27,1:27:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.92,1:27:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They think it's the money.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.96,1:27:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Scott, it's not the money at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.07,1:27:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The money is the automatic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.80,1:27:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The automatic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.57,1:27:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You build a better mousetrap, everybody's gonna buy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.53,1:27:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're gonna be rich.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.77,1:27:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I believe to pull people from the lower to the higher
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.81,1:27:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,means to encourage and give recognition
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.02,1:27:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to their creativity and their potential.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.72,1:27:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When the bird went tap, tap, tap,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.72,1:27:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I instantly went back to the bird and said,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.07,1:27:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tap, tap, tap, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.64,1:27:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment, the bird became a capitalist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.93,1:27:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ensured its survival the rest of its life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.69,1:27:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to put her in our will.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.06,1:27:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When it got it, the bird says,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.06,1:27:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta put this bird in your will,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.06,1:27:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because they live to be 100 years old,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.06,1:27:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wasn't kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.09,1:27:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the bird has to go in the will.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.09,1:27:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's the openness and the recognition.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.09,1:27:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps somebody else would not have gotten
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.09,1:27:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that the bird was trying to open a gate of communication
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.09,1:27:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,by tapping.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.09,1:27:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.09,1:27:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the bird even wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.34,1:27:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm the one that opened it as communication.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.34,1:28:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.28,1:28:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.28,1:28:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.28,1:28:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.28,1:28:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.51,1:28:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.51,1:28:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.51,1:28:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.51,1:28:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.51,1:28:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.51,1:28:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.51,1:28:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.51,1:28:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.51,1:28:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.51,1:28:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.51,1:28:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.51,1:28:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.06,1:28:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.06,1:28:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.06,1:28:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.06,1:28:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.06,1:28:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's capital.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.06,1:28:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the source of capital,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.06,1:28:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the source of electricity,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.06,1:28:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to have it come down the wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.06,1:28:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.06,1:28:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the great...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.06,1:28:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I call it genius,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.06,1:28:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because the birth of the intellect in itself is genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.06,1:28:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Freud at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.15,1:28:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Galileo.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.18,1:28:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the great geniuses of history.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.85,1:28:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the great inventors, Immanuel Kant, the categories of thought
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.03,1:28:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and the difficulty with problematic relative,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.06,1:28:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem with the difficult hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.88,1:28:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it violates,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.47,1:29:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the problematic hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.59,1:29:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to violating the categories of Immanuel Kant.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.14,1:29:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing Immanuel Kant as authoritarian instead of an authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.48,1:29:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because without structure and logic, you can't think logically.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.48,1:29:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you can't think logically, you end up writing books on postmodernism
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.97,1:29:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and Zen and postmodernism.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.93,1:29:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I defy anybody to comprehend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.02,1:29:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I bought it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.65,1:29:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated it as 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.19,1:29:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay, what does 160 look like?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.02,1:29:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.23,1:29:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I strove to understand what 160 looks like and how it thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.92,1:29:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot comprehend how it thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.25,1:29:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts out writing a foreword saying that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.71,1:29:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no reason to write a foreword because this is not really a foreword
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.32,1:29:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is it actually a foreword of anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.82,1:30:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And playing gobbledygook.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.98,1:30:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we were with Alice Carol and Lewis Carol
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.13,1:30:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and Alice's Wonderland.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.13,1:30:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mad Hatter's Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.72,1:30:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.85,1:30:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At 10.30 we'll stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.72,1:30:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You say it's time for the Mad Hatter's Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.77,1:30:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She said it's time for the Mad Hatter's Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.17,1:30:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has to make sense at all during the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.69,1:30:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back in here this minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.02,1:30:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're late, we want to kill them, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.09,1:30:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.53,1:30:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here we have the ego for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.61,1:31:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.47,1:31:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We can.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.85,1:31:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see your ego is just a little animal inside of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.50,1:31:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best thing to do instead of vilifying them is adopt them as a pet
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.38,1:31:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and encourage them to be nastier.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.57,1:31:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,More hateful, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.39,1:31:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way you own them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.52,1:31:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you own, if you own the ego, if you own the unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.26,1:31:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to project it onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.39,1:31:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You recognize that it's the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.65,1:31:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.02,1:31:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to go into intellectual tricks to try to disown it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.38,1:32:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside of you, born into you, is all the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.80,1:32:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That we just saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.89,1:32:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates anybody that cuts in front of them in traffic.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.61,1:32:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to kill people.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.93,1:32:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody that cuts in front of you in traffic deserves to die, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.48,1:32:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.30,1:32:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Road rage.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.56,1:32:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the source of road rage right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.43,1:32:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.88,1:32:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So can you defeat the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.21,1:32:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.64,1:32:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can transcend the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.38,1:32:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,People do temporarily go into very high society.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.52,1:32:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They go into very high spaces, but then they collab.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.52,1:32:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They go back out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.23,1:32:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I get a lot of letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.23,1:32:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I went into this so and so high space, and then it came, and then it left.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.86,1:32:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And bewail their fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.40,1:32:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.32,1:32:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you've transcended your karma for the time being,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.31,1:33:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but now your karma's caught up with you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.18,1:33:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There's other things you have to let go of.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.27,1:33:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When we talk about devotional non-duality, which is going to be the next book, after this one,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.14,1:33:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is transcending the ego, and, of course, our lectures have been devoted to preparing the way,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.71,1:33:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,preparing the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.39,1:33:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who understands the lectures and the videos and all gets pretty much what it's all about,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.64,1:33:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll focus more on how to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.76,1:33:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We did this morning by transcending identification, by being that which you envision,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.39,1:33:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,being that which you admire, being that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.75,1:33:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to work for it or go to artificial means.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.38,1:33:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just become that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.84,1:33:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Become that.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.84,1:34:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a letter from some guy who took issue with how I talked about transcending the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.52,1:34:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,supposedly Zen or something, and how to transcend the mind and the stages you're supposed to go through.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.88,1:34:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the old Buddhist literature has, they were obsessed with numbers.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.38,1:34:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.57,1:34:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The old Buddhist literature.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.68,1:34:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The eight ways of this and the 33 stages of our hot chip.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.97,1:34:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What stage are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.50,1:34:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at stage 27.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.85,1:34:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates a whole structure, and then you've got to struggle through the structure.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.80,1:34:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one has within it spiritual truth, and then it becomes encrusted with accretions that are distractions from the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.06,1:34:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no 33 steps to anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.09,1:34:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the instant the bird goes, you can go, didn't take 33 steps.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.53,1:34:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.89,1:35:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The bird presents its beingness, and you respond from your beingness, and it doesn't require intellection.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.22,1:35:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go through the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.52,1:35:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought, to know what you don't need to know about, we should study it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.98,1:35:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.89,1:35:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.14,1:35:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.27,1:35:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.43,1:35:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.77,1:35:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, why?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.80,1:35:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because before you can transcend a thing, you first have to master it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.11,1:35:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you can transcend logic, the ego, the whole Newtonian paradigm of reality of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.69,1:35:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.22,1:35:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.02,1:35:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the birth of the world of cause and effect, of logic and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.72,1:35:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.30,1:35:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of science is...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.88,1:36:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world of great benefit to mankind, double mankind's lifespan, cured most of the diseases, prevalent.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.02,1:36:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you still have to get out of...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.10,1:36:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off of this world somehow.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.85,1:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm worried that science is going to block all the exits.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.18,1:36:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.30,1:36:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we going to get out of here, folks?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.02,1:36:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a worry to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.35,1:36:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody wrote a book, You Can Live Forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.44,1:36:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, wasn't it...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.94,1:36:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.32,1:36:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to live forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.89,1:36:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.56,1:36:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.68,1:36:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How to make the body eternal.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.71,1:36:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, golly.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.07,1:36:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Egyptians tried it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.30,1:36:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You just cover it up with gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.85,1:36:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can't breathe inside of all that gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.89,1:36:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.56,1:36:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's the world that we're going to transcend on the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.06,1:36:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you master it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.23,1:36:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have respect for logic, reason, morality.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.47,1:36:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the whole basis of morality.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.76,1:37:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, even the secular person, of course, claims his secular...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.84,1:37:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Rights, but his rights are based on religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.84,1:37:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.84,1:37:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the rights of the Constitution of the United States, you know, the Constitution
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.84,1:37:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States calibrates the 710.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.60,1:37:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's based on the realization that the source of existence is divinity, and by virtue of
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.86,1:37:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of our existence, all men are equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.59,1:37:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They are equal by virtue of the divinity of their source, of their creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.97,1:37:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not up to anybody's vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.46,1:37:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the equality, then, the Constitution at 710 is stunningly high.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.77,1:37:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows an amazing erudition.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.78,1:37:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It knows the difference between spirituality and religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.86,1:37:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't confuse the two.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.84,1:37:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,By recognizing the reality of spirituality, it ensures our freedom from religion and freedom
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.69,1:37:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.26,1:38:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom from and freedom for.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.57,1:38:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it means that your rights are not up to the voters.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.53,1:38:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're up to the populace or some dictator because the source is the truth of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.60,1:38:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, which is the source of one's own creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.77,1:38:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.73,1:38:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely sophisticated, extremely erudite.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.53,1:38:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,710.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.53,1:38:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing on this planet has ever approached 710 as a constitution, and there's nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.52,1:38:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,out there that calibrates anywhere even in that realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.77,1:38:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did that all come about?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.52,1:38:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It came about then.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.65,1:38:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And what?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.57,1:38:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget, many of the writers of the Constitution, et cetera, the revolutionaries
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.18,1:38:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,were free thinkers.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.18,1:38:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They were not theists.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.18,1:38:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we were founded out of the freedom of the oppression of religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.57,1:38:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The Puritans came here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.27,1:38:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the structure of our society then is already set up and reinforced by man's logic, Rousseau,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.81,1:39:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,all the people that have contributed to it over the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.50,1:39:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And here are the best thinkers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.88,1:39:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And Hegel, at 425, is very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.47,1:39:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One of Hegel's principles, he was the leading philosopher of Germany of the early 1800s.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.53,1:39:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the father of philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.23,1:39:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel was very respected, and one of Hegel's principles was the principle of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.25,1:39:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.28,1:39:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.28,1:39:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It scares people.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.28,1:39:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.50,1:39:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.50,1:39:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, heh.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.50,1:39:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.50,1:39:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As the gospel says, with consciousness, we are doing, what we're getting is the calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.50,1:39:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth as compared to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.71,1:39:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As compared to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.19,1:39:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as all temperature is then, on the thermometer, are as compared to absolute zero, as compared
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.72,1:39:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to absolute zero, this temperature is at so and so.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.89,1:40:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.89,1:40:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So Hegel, then, stated a premise, which we verify every day in avec kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.34,1:40:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it on stage this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.26,1:40:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,an absolute compared to an absolute this calibrates at such-and-such a number
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.14,1:40:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to the absolute which represents truth this is either truth or
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.42,1:40:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,not truth and consciousness recognizes truth because truth has existence
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.73,1:40:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody who walks the planet radiates out an invisible energy visible energy
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.67,1:40:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,into the infinite field of consciousness which is imprinted forever it is a
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.15,1:40:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,literal fact every hair on your head is counted it's being counted right now
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.89,1:40:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,folks I thought that would after all did no it's counted right now because that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.81,1:41:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which you are is already as you see positioned by the power of the field as
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.36,1:41:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your configuration as you karmically come into this world your propensities
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.59,1:41:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your lecture dislikes your debts etc are automatically every hair on your
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.36,1:41:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,head
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.47,1:41:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,head is already counting itself automatically, not as an external moralistic judge, but as
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.96,1:41:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a consequence of the reality of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.76,1:41:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So Hegel's principle is extraordinarily important, important, because we'll see what happens
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.63,1:41:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when you negate the principle of the absolute as we get farther down the list.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.07,1:41:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you have Kant, the categories of logic, you see logic and reason have a certain dialectic.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.92,1:41:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just say anything you want to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.57,1:42:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain rules of logic and ethics and etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.15,1:42:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And Kant set up the categories, and to violate these categories means that you're mixing
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.11,1:42:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.34,1:42:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you mix levels, you're ignoring context, and therefore much of relativistic epistemology
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.00,1:42:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.07,1:42:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, much of the problematic pedantry of relativistic epistemology is based on the
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.71,1:42:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,extreme violation of all these rules and regulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.09,1:42:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which calibrates at 160 is not higher than the truth, and Kant at 460, 160 is not
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.06,1:42:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than 460.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.27,1:42:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to know whether relativistic epistemology is a philosophy of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.10,1:42:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what does relativism say?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.77,1:42:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It says there are no absolutes, so anything is anything we want to say it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.85,1:42:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pedastry is good and legal.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:55.97,1:42:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Men should pursue young boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.73,1:43:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have organizations that support them legally.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.47,1:43:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything can mean anything you want it to mean, because everything is just a semantic
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.48,1:43:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,convenience, and thereby the society collapses into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.90,1:43:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Society collapses into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.90,1:43:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Society collapses into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.90,1:43:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Society collapses into chaos.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.90,1:43:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Society collapses because, without structure, nothing has any meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.40,1:43:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything can mean anything I want it to mean, then I'll take my clothes off now and
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.67,1:43:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,murder somebody and that's all freedom of expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.40,1:43:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's to say it's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.80,1:43:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no absolute...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.14,1:43:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's no structure to society, and, of course, we wouldn't be able to do kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.42,1:43:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.42,1:43:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Kant's categories, then, are important, and by following all of these the great scientists...the
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.92,1:43:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,scientists arose by following logic and mathematics which is a refinement of
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.07,1:44:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,logic and so all collectively they calibrate around 450 or something and if
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.06,1:44:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you then we come to Marx and if you remove Marx from the list of the entire
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.94,1:44:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,list that the whole list goes from 450 to 460 Wow then of course Engels is at
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.65,1:44:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,200 so he didn't help a lot he's not dragging his feet but he's going to see
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.89,1:44:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,himself so I never calibrated it without marks and angles but you see they're the
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.31,1:44:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,lowest of all and what is the difficulty with marks well marks had an unresolved
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.39,1:44:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,notable complex we'll verify what I'm saying 50 years I was a psychoanalyst I
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.89,1:44:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,mean I can read it from I can take it a glance and say what that person's
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.31,1:44:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,conflicts is and mother was earlier life was
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.51,1:44:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.51,1:44:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.90,1:44:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx obviously had an unresolved edible complex, he had a violent hostility towards authority,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.05,1:45:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so he rebelled against Hegel, and he wrote really what is a complete violation and desecration
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.71,1:45:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.71,1:45:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to see a violation and desecration of truth, it beats relativism at Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.14,1:45:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you haven't read Marx, you really should, because if you want to know what horrible
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.18,1:45:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,error is, you've got to get familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.82,1:45:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the error, and why does it have such a devastating downside?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.14,1:45:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the writing of Marx, you see, the pen is mightier than the sword, so to know
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.48,1:45:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what is truth, then, makes the difference between survival and death, so it's not exactly
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.47,1:45:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,just an intellectual nicety.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.36,1:45:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference, to know the difference between truth and falsehood is the difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.60,1:45:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,life and death.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.44,1:45:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The writings of this man cost the lives of 100 million people across Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.34,1:45:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The world, huh, 100 million, in my lifetime, Stalin put to death 30 million, so the price
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.22,1:46:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of not being able to discern truth from falsehood is death, and war, devastation, nuclear bombs,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.36,1:46:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and devastation.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.81,1:46:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that he's at 130, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.48,1:46:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what was the problem with the man?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.81,1:46:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't handle, he misidentified authority as authoritarianism.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.90,1:46:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is a common mistake in today's society, of rebellion is really sort of an adolescent
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.47,1:46:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,immaturity, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.17,1:46:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marx misinterpreted, and what he did was create a duality, see, the way to truth is
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.26,1:46:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,through non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.89,1:46:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the maximum duality would then be to create everything in terms of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:45.46,1:46:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallout of this in our society is what is tearing apart the fabric of our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.85,1:47:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The dualistic projection onto everything in the world of perpetrator-victim, perpetrator-victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.47,1:47:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If I take the perpetrator-victim paradigm, I can apply it to anything, anytime, anywhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.56,1:47:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can do it retroactively in history, and I can spend a whole lifetime doing make-wrongs
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.84,1:47:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in history.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.56,1:47:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it with everything in society.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.02,1:47:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you end up with a contentious society, you end up with sedition, you know, sedition
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.64,1:47:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,disguised as patriotism, or homicide disguised as religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.39,1:47:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything can be whatever you say it is, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.03,1:47:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the perpetrator-victim then appeals to being the martyr, appeals to being the victim,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.50,1:47:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it appeals to blame.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.07,1:47:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it causes repression of that which is within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.81,1:48:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So from a psychoanalytic viewpoint, it is very sick.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.56,1:48:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't transcend something that you haven't owned.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.96,1:48:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if you repress it, then you project it into the world and you see it out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.18,1:48:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why a paranoid never gets better.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.51,1:48:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And why all the narcissistic messianic megalomaniacs who calibrated at 35, such as Stalin and Hitler
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.01,1:48:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and all, were so vicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.25,1:48:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed people.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.25,1:48:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed people.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.01,1:48:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They killed people.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.77,1:48:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler's best generals, what he did was he exterminated them all, and Stalin did the
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.65,1:48:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.65,1:48:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Stalin did the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.59,1:48:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the 135 people that were there when Stalin was elected, commissar or whatever the hell
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.10,1:48:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it was, of the 135, something like 98 were executed.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.69,1:48:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So in return for loyalty, he executed you.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.23,1:48:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:56.52,1:49:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the appeal of that kind of thinking then is not too attractive.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.11,1:49:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,130 just doesn't appeal to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.68,1:49:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, if you pick, you can picture yourself, the payoff, the juice that you get
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.42,1:49:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,out of martyrdom, that you're being wronged, that you're being perpetrated against.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.57,1:49:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the perpetrator, victim mode of thinking becomes a meme.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.11,1:49:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,M-E-M-E.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.11,1:49:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody not familiar with meme?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.11,1:49:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Meme?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.23,1:49:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Meme is like a virus, a thought that is contagious.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.56,1:49:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And it becomes a saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.32,1:49:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.14,1:49:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And so everybody's talking about rights and being a victim and all this, and dividing
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.13,1:49:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,all of society then into perpetrator, victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.81,1:49:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Marx did it with capitalism, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.82,1:49:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, it was tried out.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.67,1:49:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And Russia tried it out for a long time, and you see what happened with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.10,1:49:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so it's been a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.18,1:49:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.89,1:50:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrating the levels of consciousness then is very, very informative.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.11,1:50:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Karl Marx have an unresolved double complex?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.38,1:50:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.19,1:50:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.19,1:50:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He did indeed resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.19,1:50:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.19,1:50:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,After 50 years of psychoanalysis, I couldn't even.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.23,1:50:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you could tell what's wrong with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.81,1:50:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the adolescent rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.05,1:50:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, the adolescent rebellion appealed to a lot of adolescents.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.40,1:50:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So he attracted a lot of adolescents.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.90,1:50:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see violence and bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.44,1:50:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And guillotine coming out of all this kind of thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.21,1:50:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I say, this guy here at 200 didn't help much.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.21,1:50:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels, he just sort of, the fall guy, went along with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.00,1:50:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.00,1:50:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So then erudition means the 400s, why are they important?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.81,1:50:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they are science, logic, and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.98,1:50:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the shoot-off from which the Newtonian paradigm of reality is a very great advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.59,1:50:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Many parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.47,1:51:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.50,1:51:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It lives on less than $2 a day.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.18,1:51:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic and reason and the categories of abstraction are not dominant in their society.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.18,1:51:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all Okinawans think logic and reason haven't been sweetly balanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.07,1:51:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As always, I hope you have a good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:28.03,1:51:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe we'll continue.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.97,1:51:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing day and night?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.47,1:51:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's why I don't talk about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.97,1:51:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've deployed people like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.21,1:51:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And they didn't show up for work yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.67,1:51:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're sitting there, why?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.60,1:51:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.60,1:51:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But after you've mastered it, after you've learned to be orderly and on time and reliable
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.90,1:52:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and et cetera, then you can become sloppy again because you've transcended it, not because
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.55,1:52:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you haven't gotten there yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.34,1:52:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you see Sir Isaac Newton, the differential calculus.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.76,1:52:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the real master of mathematics in the modern world was Sir Isaac Newton and his development
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.23,1:52:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the differential calculus out of which all advanced mathematics and sciences evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.15,1:52:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we owe these men all the conveniences that we have today.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.10,1:52:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The healing from illness, half of us in this audience are probably dead already, if there
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.11,1:52:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,were that many even left to die because childhood diseases killed us off and when I was in practice
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.38,1:52:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,out of medical school, my first job was the hospital for infectious diseases.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.47,1:52:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.97,1:52:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Typhoid and malaria and diphtheria, measles and smallpox and the dread disease where they
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.40,1:52:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,bring the kid in and one arm is down, what's the name of that one?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.77,1:53:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Polio.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.38,1:53:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Polio, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.38,1:53:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So they bring the kid in like this in the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.35,1:53:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So here I'm an intern and the doctor who's in charge has an alcohol problem, he's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.69,1:53:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's me all alone with the family, the diagnosis, so I got to, you know, do a spinal
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.81,1:53:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tap on the kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.81,1:53:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Handle the family, spin the, spin it down, see what the white soles are and then tell
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.15,1:53:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the family the news and of course the look on my face, they got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.81,1:53:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember many a time I'd walk into the waiting room.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.35,1:53:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't have to go through that anymore thanks to these men.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.93,1:53:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point of putting them down which relativism tends to do, just, you know, look
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.31,1:53:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,down on science and logic and research.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.72,1:54:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic and reason and the downside of that kind of thinking is that the school room of
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.84,1:54:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,1900 calibrated at 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.93,1:54:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The school room of today calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.18,1:54:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore progressive education is regressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.26,1:54:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's time to take responsibility, Billy.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.61,1:54:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to stop writing graffiti and stop giving them an A for graffiti in class.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.81,1:54:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They have classes in graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.15,1:54:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.26,1:54:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is not to become better at graffiti, the problem is to transcend graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:36.14,1:54:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So that kind of thinkingness has a deleterious.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.39,1:54:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to respect then the integrity of the 400s and the intellect and at the same
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.38,1:54:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,time as spiritual students, we have to transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.07,1:54:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So first you master it, then you transcend it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:52.15,1:54:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you begin to see that this is a way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.26,1:54:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Descartes' res internum.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.31,1:54:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.31,1:55:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . the way of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:04.06,1:55:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the basic problem with duality is the resumption that the way my mind thinks is the way it
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.03,1:55:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.14,1:55:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If I see this happen and this happen, my mind says causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:16.64,1:55:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I think causality is a principle of nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.61,1:55:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality is a principle of res cogitons.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.93,1:55:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.57,1:55:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To see victim and perpetrator is all in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.97,1:55:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in your head. There's no
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.97,1:55:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,victims and no perpetrators out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.92,1:55:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The big tree
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.73,1:55:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,falls on the little tree
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.39,1:55:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because it got blown over by the wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.67,1:55:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean the little tree is the
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.32,1:55:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,victim. The big tree is a
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.28,1:55:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,perpetrator. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.22,1:55:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.60,1:55:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,differentiate res cogitans
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.86,1:55:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,from res externa,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.86,1:55:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the way the world is, the way nature
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.68,1:55:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is, is the big jump.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.90,1:56:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the big jump.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.93,1:56:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Very seldom, frankly, is it made.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.44,1:56:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why enlightenment is not coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:06.81,1:56:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It presumes that the
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.10,1:56:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,mentation, then, is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.89,1:56:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, our problem,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.18,1:56:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because a group like this is very erudite
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.21,1:56:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with, because
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.09,1:56:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellect, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.43,1:56:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on the one hand is the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.02,1:56:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand is the springboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.94,1:56:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we hear about spirituality, we begin
Dialogue: 0,1:56:24.25,1:56:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to study it, we read the great masters,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.17,1:56:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to contemplate
Dialogue: 0,1:56:28.51,1:56:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it. And now, we want
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.22,1:56:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to get beyond, how do you get beyond thinkingness?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.48,1:56:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do we get beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.50,1:56:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.53,1:56:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do we get beyond thinkingness?
